#Explain list comprehension vs generator expressions.

1.List Comprehension
Creates the entire list in memory at once.
squares = [x*x for x in range(5)]
print(squares)
o/p-->[0, 1, 4, 9, 16]-->Lots of memory.
Everything is stored immediately.

2.Generator Expression
Produces values one at a time when needed.
Water dispenser.
Press button
↓
Get one bottle
Only produces what you need
squares = (x*x for x in range(5))
print(squares)
o/p-->[0, 1, 4, 9, 16]-->much less memory.
generators produce values one by one
